{{notability|date=May 2018}}
{{italic title}}
'''''Gladiators – Heroes of the Colosseum''''' is an international [[travelling exhibition]] from Italy on Roman [[gladiator]]s. The exhibition portrays the [[Roman Empire]] and the [[gladiator]] games.<ref name=jonkoping>{{Cite web|url=https://jkpg.com/en/jonkoping-huskvarna/gladiators/|title=Gladiators|website=jkpg.com|language=en|access-date=2018-04-20}}</ref>

The exhibition has so far been exhibited at [[Aarhus]], Denmark, at [[Ottawa]], Canada, and at the [[Queensland Museum]] in [[Brisbane]], Australia,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gladiators.qm.qld.gov.au/About|title=About - Gladiators: Heroes of the Colosseum|website=www.gladiators.qm.qld.gov.au|accessdate=17 May 2018}}</ref> and is currently being displayed in [[Jönköping]], Sweden until August 2018,<ref name=jonkoping/> after which it will be held at the Musée de la Romanité in [[Nîmes]], France.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/travel/2018/apr/17/nimes-france-great-roman-games-re-enactment-spectacular-gladiators-spartacus|title=‘I’m Spartacus!’: gladiators galore at Nîmes’ Great Roman Games|first=Jon|last=Bryant|date=17 April 2018|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=17 May 2018}}</ref> So far it has been seen by over 500,000 attendees.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}} For every new exhibition, new segments are added.{{citation needed|date=May 2018}}

