{{Infobox language family |name=Koiarian |altname=Koiari – Managalas Plateau |region=Southeastern peninsula of {{nowrap|[[New Guinea]]}} |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[Trans–New Guinea languages|Trans–New Guinea]] |fam2=[[Papuan Peninsula languages|Papuan Peninsula]] |fam3=Owen Stanley Range<ref>[https://sites.google.com/site/newguineaworld/families/trans-new-guinea/papuan-peninsula/owen-stanley-range New Guinea World, Owen Stanley Range]</ref> |child1=Koiaric |child2=Baraic |glotto=koia1260 |glottorefname=Koiarian }}
The '''Koiarian languages''' {{IPAc-en|k|ɔɪ|ˈ|ɑr|i|ən}}<ref>Laurie Bauer, 2007, ''The Linguistics Student’s Handbook'', Edinburgh</ref> Koiari are a small family of [[Trans&ndash;New Guinea languages]] spoken in the "[[Bird's Tail]]" (southeastern peninsula) of New Guinea. They are sometimes included in a speculative [[Southeast Papuan languages|Southeast Papuan]] branch of Trans&ndash;New Guinea (TNG), but the Southeast Papuan families have not been shown to be any more closely related to each other than they are to other TNG families.
The languages are: * Koiaric branch: [[Grass Koiari language|Grass Koiari]], [[Mountain Koiari language|Mountain Koiari]]–[[Koitabu language|Koitabu]] * Baraic branch: [[Barai language|Barai]]–[[Namiae language|Namiae]], [[Ese language|Ese]] (Managalasi), [[Ömie language|Ömie]]
Pronouns are:
:{| ! !!sg!!pl |- !1 |?||*no |- !2 |*a||*ya |- !3 |*ahu||*yabu |}
1sg is Koiaric *da (= nda?) or maybe *di, Baraic *na.
